These types of approaches have used existing rat lethality data, as described in ISO 13344 [14] or more

recently, based on estimates of human incapacitation, as described in ISO 13571 [6] (for which FED = 1

represents incapacitation of 50% of the exposed population), since the point at which the fire victims can

no longer affect their own escape is the point where their chance of survival diminishes. The Purser model,

